{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893916157,"sessionID":"ses_2847bed05ffeMVU8Kgsi7SMCU3","part":{"id":"prt_d7b86a991001jcctMcIg1iNzac","messageID":"msg_d7b84a6ce001N7cTdJBOGgdqHN","sessionID":"ses_2847bed05ffeMVU8Kgsi7SMCU3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-bdf7ef0987e04a2a9c94f812d37d83b8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/example/design.md","content":"# AR-037: PCAP Analyzer Example Application\n\n## Overview\n\nA Python example application demonstrating AgentCube SDK usage for PCAP (packet capture) file analysis. The application uses `CodeInterpreterClient` to execute network analysis tools and Python scripts in an isolated sandbox environment.\n\n| Attribute | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| Module | example |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| SDK | agentcube-sdk |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\nexample/\n├── pcap-analyzer/\n│   ├── design.md              # This document\n│   ├── spec.md                # Specification\n│   ├── main.py                # Entry point\n│   ├── analyzer.py            # Core analyzer logic\n│   ├── parsers/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── tcp_parser.py      # TCP stream parser\n│   │   ├── http_parser.py     # HTTP traffic parser\n│   │   └── dns_parser.py      # DNS query parser\n│   ├── utils/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── file_utils.py      # File handling utilities\n│   │   └── report_utils.py    # Report generation\n│   ├── requirements.txt       # Dependencies\n│   ├── README.md              # Usage documentation\n│   └── tests/\n│   │   ├── test_analyzer.py\n│   │   ├── test_tcp_parser.py\n│   │   └── test_http_parser.py\n│   └── sample_data/\n│   │   ├── sample.pcap        # Sample PCAP file for testing\n│   │   └── expected_output.json\n```\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        PCAP Analyzer Example                              │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                          │\n│   ┌─────────────────┐                                                    │\n│   │    main.py      │                                                    │\n│   │  (CLI Entry)    │                                                    │\n│   └────────┬────────┘                                                    │\n│            │                                                             │\n│            ▼                                                             │\n│   ┌─────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│   │   analyzer.py   │────▶│        AgentCube SDK                  │     │\n│   │                 │     │  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐  │     │\n│   │  - load_pcap()  │     │  │    CodeInterpreterClient        │  │     │\n│   │  - analyze()    │     │  │                                 │  │     │\n│   │  - generate_    │     │  │  - execute_command()            │  │     │\n│   │    report()     │     │  │  - run_code()                   │  │     │\n│   └────────┬────────┘     │  │  - upload_file()                │  │     │\n│            │              │  │  - download_file()              │  │     │\n│            ▼              │  └─────────────────────────────────┘  │     │\n│   ┌─────────────────┐     └──────────────────┬────────────────────┘     │\n│   │    parsers/     │                        │                          │\n│   │                 │                        ▼                          │\n│   │  - tcp_parser   │     ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│   │  - http_parser  │     │          Sandbox Pod                   │     │\n│   │  - dns_parser   │     │  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐  │     │\n│   └────────┬────────┘     │  │           PicoD                 │  │     │\n│            │              │  │                                 │  │     │\n│            ▼              │  │  - tshark CLI                   │  │     │\n│   ┌─────────────────┐     │  │  - tcpdump CLI                  │  │     │\n│   │    utils/       │     │  │  - Python runtime               │  │     │\n│   │                 │     │  │  - scapy library                │  │     │\n│   │  - file_utils   │     │  │  - pyshark library              │  │     │\n│   │  - report_utils │     │  └─────────────────────────────────┘  │     │\n│   └─────────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n│                                                                          │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Flow Diagram\n\n```\n┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         PCAP Analysis Flow                                 │\n├───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                            │\n│   1. Initialize                                                            │\n│   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│   │  Client = CodeInterpreterClient(                                     │ │\n│   │      name=\"pcap-analyzer\",                                           │ │\n│   │      ttl=3600                                                        │ │\n│   │  )                                                                   │ │\n│   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                                                                            │\n│   2. Upload PCAP                                                           │\n│   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│   │  client.upload_file(\"traffic.pcap\", \"/workspace/traffic.pcap\")       │ │\n│   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                                                                            │\n│   3. Run Analysis Scripts                                                  │\n│   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│   │  # Use tshark to extract fields                                      │ │\n│   │  client.execute_command(                                             │ │\n│   │      \"tshark -r traffic.pcap -Y tcp -T fields ...\"                   │ │\n│   │  )                                                                   │ │\n│   │                                                                      │ │\n│   │  # Run Python analysis                                               │ │\n│   │  client.run_code(\"python\", analyze_script)                           │ │\n│   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                                                                            │\n│   4. Download Results                                                      │\n│   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│   │  client.download_file(\"/workspace/report.json\", \"report.json\")       │ │\n│   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                                                                            │\n│   5. Cleanup                                                               │\n│   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│   │  client.stop()  # or context manager exit                            │ │\n│   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                                                                            │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Configuration\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass AnalyzerConfig:\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n    namespace: str = \"default\"\n    session_name: str = \"pcap-analyzer\"\n    ttl: int = 3600\n    timeout: int = 120\n    verbose: bool = False\n    output_format: str = \"json\"\n```\n\n### Analysis Result Types\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any\n\n@dataclass\nclass PacketSummary:\n    timestamp: datetime\n    source_ip: str\n    source_port: int\n    dest_ip: str\n    dest_port: int\n    protocol: str\n    length: int\n    flags: Optional[str] = None\n\n@dataclass\nclass TCPStream:\n    stream_id: int\n    packets: List[PacketSummary]\n    bytes_sent: int\n    bytes_recv: int\n    duration_ms: float\n    state: str\n\n@dataclass\nclass HTTPTransaction:\n    request_time: datetime\n    method: str\n    url: str\n    host: str\n    response_code: int\n    response_time_ms: float\n    content_length: int\n\n@dataclass\nclass AnalysisReport:\n    pcap_file: str\n    analysis_time: datetime\n    total_packets: int\n    protocols: Dict[str, int]\n    tcp_streams: List[TCPStream]\n    http_transactions: List[HTTPTransaction]\n    top_sources: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n    top_destinations: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n    anomalies: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Analyzer Interface\n\n```python\nfrom abc import ABC, abstractmethod\nfrom typing import Optional, List\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nclass PCAPAnalyzerInterface(ABC):\n    @abstractmethod\n    def load_pcap(self, file_path: Path) -> None:\n        pass\n    \n    @abstractmethod\n    def get_packet_summary(self) -> List[PacketSummary]:\n        pass\n    \n    @abstractmethod\n    def get_tcp_streams(self) -> List[TCPStream]:\n        pass\n    \n    @abstractmethod\n    def get_http_transactions(self) -> List[HTTPTransaction]:\n        pass\n    \n    @abstractmethod\n    def generate_report(self, output_format: str = \"json\") -> str:\n        pass\n```\n\n### Analyzer Implementation\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nclass PCAPAnalyzer(PCAPAnalyzerInterface):\n    def __init__(self, config: AnalyzerConfig):\n        self.config = config\n        self._client: Optional[CodeInterpreterClient] = None\n    \n    def connect(self) -> None:\n        self._client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n            name=self.config.session_name,\n            namespace=self.config.namespace,\n            ttl=self.config.ttl,\n            router_url=self.config.router_url,\n            workload_manager_url=self.config.workload_manager_url,\n            verbose=self.config.verbose,\n        )\n        self._client.__enter__()\n    \n    def disconnect(self) -> None:\n        if self._client:\n            self._client.stop()\n            self._client = None\n    \n    def load_pcap(self, file_path: Path) -> None:\n        if not self._client:\n            raise RuntimeError(\"Not connected\")\n        self._client.upload_file(\n            str(file_path),\n            f\"/workspace/{file_path.name}\"\n        )\n        self._pcap_remote_path = f\"/workspace/{file_path.name}\"\n    \n    def get_packet_summary(self) -> List[PacketSummary]:\n        script = '''\nimport json\nfrom scapy.all import rdpcap\n\npackets = rdpcap(\"{pcap_path}\")\nsummary = []\nfor pkt in packets:\n    if hasattr(pkt, 'IP'):\n        summary.append({\n            \"timestamp\": float(pkt.time),\n            \"source_ip\": pkt.IP.src,\n            \"dest_ip\": pkt.IP.dst,\n            \"protocol\": pkt.IP.proto,\n            \"length\": len(pkt)\n        })\nprint(json.dumps(summary))\n'''\n        result = self._client.run_code(\n            \"python\",\n            script.format(pcap_path=self._pcap_remote_path),\n            timeout=self.config.timeout\n        )\n        return self._parse_summary(result)\n    \n    def get_tcp_streams(self) -> List[TCPStream]:\n        result = self._client.execute_command(\n            f\"tshark -r {self._pcap_remote_path} -z conv,tcp\",\n            timeout=self.config.timeout\n        )\n        return self._parse_tcp_conversations(result)\n    \n    def get_http_transactions(self) -> List[HTTPTransaction]:\n        result = self._client.execute_command(\n            f\"tshark -r {self._pcap_remote_path} -Y http -T fields \"\n            \"-e frame.time -e http.request.method -e http.host \"\n            \"-e http.request.uri -e http.response.code\",\n            timeout=self.config.timeout\n        )\n        return self._parse_http(result)\n    \n    def generate_report(self, output_format: str = \"json\") -> str:\n        report = AnalysisReport(\n            pcap_file=self._pcap_remote_path,\n            analysis_time=datetime.now(),\n            total_packets=len(self.get_packet_summary()),\n            protocols=self._get_protocol_stats(),\n            tcp_streams=self.get_tcp_streams(),\n            http_transactions=self.get_http_transactions(),\n            top_sources=self._get_top_sources(),\n            top_destinations=self._get_top_destinations(),\n            anomalies=self._detect_anomalies(),\n        )\n        \n        if output_format == \"json\":\n            return json.dumps(asdict(report), indent=2)\n        elif output_format == \"html\":\n            return self._generate_html_report(report)\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported format: {output_format}\")\n```\n\n### CLI Interface\n\n```python\nimport typer\n\napp = typer.Typer()\n\n@app.command()\ndef analyze(\n    pcap_file: Path = typer.Argument(..., help=\"PCAP file to analyze\"),\n    router_url: str = typer.Option(None, help=\"Router URL\"),\n    output_format: str = typer.Option(\"json\", help=\"Output format (json/html)\"),\n    output_file: Path = typer.Option(None, help=\"Output file path\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, help=\"Verbose output\"),\n):\n    config = AnalyzerConfig(\n        router_url=router_url,\n        verbose=verbose,\n        output_format=output_format,\n    )\n    \n    analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(config)\n    try:\n        analyzer.connect()\n        analyzer.load_pcap(pcap_file)\n        report = analyzer.generate_report(output_format)\n        \n        if output_file:\n            output_file.write_text(report)\n        else:\n            print(report)\n    finally:\n        analyzer.disconnect()\n\n@app.command()\ndef streams(\n    pcap_file: Path = typer.Argument(..., help=\"PCAP file\"),\n    router_url: str = typer.Option(None, help=\"Router URL\"),\n):\n    config = AnalyzerConfig(router_url=router_url)\n    analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(config)\n    try:\n        analyzer.connect()\n        analyzer.load_pcap(pcap_file)\n        streams = analyzer.get_tcp_streams()\n        for stream in streams:\n            print(f\"Stream {stream.stream_id}: {stream.bytes_sent}/{stream.bytes_recv} bytes\")\n    finally:\n        analyzer.disconnect()\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app()\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Classes\n\n```python\nclass AnalyzerError(Exception):\n    pass\n\nclass ConnectionError(AnalyzerError):\n    def __init__(self, message: str, original_error: Exception):\n        super().__init__(f\"Connection failed: {message}\")\n        self.original_error = original_error\n\nclass PCAPParseError(AnalyzerError):\n    def __init__(self, pcap_file: str, detail: str):\n        super().__init__(f\"Failed to parse {pcap_file}: {detail}\")\n        self.pcap_file = pcap_file\n\nclass ToolNotAvailableError(AnalyzerError):\n    def __init__(self, tool_name: str):\n        super().__init__(f\"Required tool '{tool_name}' not available in sandbox\")\n        self.tool_name = tool_name\n\nclass TimeoutError(AnalyzerError):\n    def __init__(self, operation: str, timeout_seconds: int):\n        super().__init__(f\"Operation '{operation}' timed out after {timeout_seconds}s\")\n        self.operation = operation\n```\n\n### Error Handling Pattern\n\n```python\ndef safe_analyze(analyzer: PCAPAnalyzer, pcap_file: Path) -> Optional[AnalysisReport]:\n    try:\n        analyzer.connect()\n        analyzer.load_pcap(pcap_file)\n        return analyzer.generate_report()\n    except ConnectionError as e:\n        logger.error(f\"Failed to connect to sandbox: {e}\")\n        return None\n    except PCAPParseError as e:\n        logger.error(f\"Invalid PCAP file: {e}\")\n        return None\n    except ToolNotAvailableError as e:\n        logger.error(f\"Sandbox missing tool: {e.tool_name}\")\n        logger.info(\"Ensure sandbox image includes tshark, tcpdump, scapy\")\n        return None\n    except TimeoutError as e:\n        logger.warning(f\"Analysis took too long, try larger timeout\")\n        return None\n    finally:\n        analyzer.disconnect()\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import Mock, patch, MagicMock\n\nclass TestPCAPAnalyzer:\n    @pytest.fixture\n    def mock_client(self):\n        client = Mock(spec=CodeInterpreterClient)\n        client.__enter__ = Mock(return_value=client)\n        client.__exit__ = Mock(return_value=False)\n        return client\n    \n    @pytest.fixture\n    def analyzer(self, mock_client):\n        config = AnalyzerConfig(router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n        analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(config)\n        analyzer._client = mock_client\n        return analyzer\n    \n    def test_load_pcap_success(self, analyzer, mock_client):\n        pcap_path = Path(\"test.pcap\")\n        analyzer.load_pcap(pcap_path)\n        mock_client.upload_file.assert_called_once_with(\n            \"test.pcap\", \"/workspace/test.pcap\"\n        )\n    \n    def test_get_packet_summary(self, analyzer, mock_client):\n        mock_client.run_code.return_value = json.dumps([\n            {\"timestamp\": 1234.5, \"source_ip\": \"10.0.0.1\", \n             \"dest_ip\": \"10.0.0.2\", \"protocol\": 6, \"length\": 100}\n        ])\n        \n        summary = analyzer.get_packet_summary()\n        assert len(summary) == 1\n        assert summary[0].source_ip == \"10.0.0.1\"\n    \n    def test_not_connected_raises(self):\n        analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(AnalyzerConfig())\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"Not connected\"):\n            analyzer.load_pcap(Path(\"test.pcap\"))\n    \n    def test_context_manager_cleanup(self):\n        config = AnalyzerConfig(router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n        with PCAPAnalyzer(config) as analyzer:\n            analyzer.load_pcap(Path(\"test.pcap\"))\n        assert analyzer._client is None\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nimport subprocess\nimport time\nimport requests\n\n@pytest.fixture(scope=\"module\")\ndef sandbox_environment():\n    subprocess.run([\"kubectl\", \"apply\", \"-f\", \"sandbox.yaml\"])\n    time.sleep(30)\n    yield\n    subprocess.run([\"kubectl\", \"delete\", \"-f\", \"sandbox.yaml\"])\n\nclass TestPCAPAnalyzerIntegration:\n    def test_real_pcap_analysis(self, sandbox_environment, tmp_path):\n        pcap_file = tmp_path / \"sample.pcap\"\n        pcap_file.write_bytes(SAMPLE_PCAP_DATA)\n        \n        config = AnalyzerConfig(\n            router_url=\"http://router.default.svc:8080\",\n            ttl=600,\n        )\n        \n        analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(config)\n        analyzer.connect()\n        analyzer.load_pcap(pcap_file)\n        \n        summary = analyzer.get_packet_summary()\n        assert len(summary) > 0\n        \n        streams = analyzer.get_tcp_streams()\n        assert len(streams) >= 0\n        \n        analyzer.disconnect()\n    \n    def test_large_pcap_timeout(self, sandbox_environment, tmp_path):\n        large_pcap = create_large_pcap(tmp_path, 10000)\n        \n        config = AnalyzerConfig(\n            router_url=\"http://router.default.svc:8080\",\n            timeout=30,\n        )\n        \n        analyzer = PCAPAnalyzer(config)\n        analyzer.connect()\n        analyzer.load_pcap(large_pcap)\n        \n        with pytest.raises(TimeoutError):\n            analyzer.get_packet_summary()\n        \n        analyzer.disconnect()\n```\n\n### End-to-End Tests\n\n```python\nclass TestCLI:\n    def test_analyze_command(self, tmp_path):\n        pcap_file = tmp_path / \"test.pcap\"\n        output_file = tmp_path / \"report.json\"\n        \n        result = subprocess.run([\n            \"python\", \"-m\", \"pcap_analyzer\", \"analyze\",\n            str(pcap_file),\n            \"--router-url\", \"http://localhost:8080\",\n            \"--output-file\", str(output_file),\n        ], capture_output=True)\n        \n        assert result.returncode == 0\n        assert output_file.exists()\n        report = json.loads(output_file.read_text())\n        assert \"total_packets\" in report\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### requirements.txt\n\n```text\nagentcube-sdk>=1.0.0\ntyper>=0.9.0\npydantic>=2.0.0\nrich>=13.0.0\n```\n\n### Sandbox Image Requirements\n\nThe sandbox pod image must include:\n\n```text\ntshark>=4.0.0\ntcpdump>=4.9.0\npython3>=3.10\nscapy>=2.5.0\npyshark>=0.4.3\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|---------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | None | Router endpoint URL |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | None | Workload manager URL |\n| `ANALYZER_NAMESPACE` | default | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `ANALYZER_TTL` | 3600 | Session TTL in seconds |\n| `ANALYZER_TIMEOUT` | 120 | Analysis timeout in seconds |\n\n### CLI Options\n\n| Option | Default | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `--router-url` | None | Router URL override |\n| `--namespace` | default | Namespace override |\n| `--ttl` | 3600 | Session TTL |\n| `--timeout` | 120 | Operation timeout |\n| `--output-format` | json | Output format (json/html) |\n| `--verbose` | False | Enable debug logging |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/main.py` - CLI entry point\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/analyzer.py` - Core analyzer class\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/parsers/tcp_parser.py` - TCP stream parser\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/parsers/http_parser.py` - HTTP transaction parser\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/parsers/dns_parser.py` - DNS query parser\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/utils/file_utils.py` - File utilities\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/utils/report_utils.py` - Report generation\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` - Dependencies\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` - Usage documentation\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/tests/test_analyzer.py` - Analyzer tests\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/tests/test_parsers.py` - Parser tests\n- [ ] `example/pcap-analyzer/sample_data/sample.pcap` - Test data\n- [ ] Integration test with real sandbox\n- [ ] Documentation with usage examples\n\n---\n\n## Metrics\n\n### Performance Targets\n\n| Metric | Target |\n|--------|--------|\n| Small PCAP (<1000 packets) analysis | < 5s |\n| Medium PCAP (1000-10000 packets) | < 30s |\n| Large PCAP (>10000 packets) | < 120s |\n| Memory usage in sandbox | < 512MB |\n\n### Observability\n\n```python\nimport time\nfrom functools import wraps\n\ndef timed_operation(operation_name: str):\n    def decorator(func):\n        @wraps(func)\n        def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):\n            start = time.time()\n            try:\n                result = func(*args, **kwargs)\n                duration = time.time() - start\n                logger.info(f\"{operation_name} completed in {duration:.2f}s\")\n                return result\n            except Exception as e:\n                duration = time.time() - start\n                logger.error(f\"{operation_name} failed after {duration:.2f}s: {e}\")\n                raise\n        return wrapper\n    return decorator\n```\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Sandbox Isolation\n\n- All PCAP analysis runs in isolated sandbox pod\n- No direct filesystem access from analyzer host\n- Network tools confined to sandbox network namespace\n\n### Data Handling\n\n- PCAP files uploaded via secure channel (HTTPS)\n- Session-based authentication via `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- Automatic cleanup of uploaded files on session termination\n\n### Resource Limits\n\n- Maximum PCAP file size: configurable via SDK\n- Maximum execution time: configurable timeout\n- Memory limits enforced by sandbox pod spec\n\n---\n\n## Example Usage\n\n### Basic Analysis\n\n```python\nfrom pcap_analyzer import PCAPAnalyzer, AnalyzerConfig\n\nconfig = AnalyzerConfig(router_url=\"http://router.example.com:8080\")\n\nwith PCAPAnalyzer(config) as analyzer:\n    analyzer.load_pcap(\"network_traffic.pcap\")\n    \n    print(f\"Total packets: {len(analyzer.get_packet_summary())}\")\n    \n    for stream in analyzer.get_tcp_streams():\n        print(f\"TCP Stream {stream.stream_id}: {stream.state}\")\n    \n    report = analyzer.generate_report()\n    print(report)\n```\n\n### CLI Usage\n\n```bash\n# Analyze a PCAP file\npython -m pcap_analyzer analyze traffic.pcap \\\n    --router-url http://router:8080 \\\n    --output-format json \\\n    --output-file report.json\n\n# List TCP streams\npython -m pcap_analyzer streams traffic.pcap \\\n    --router-url http://router:8080\n\n# Verbose analysis\npython -m pcap_analyzer analyze traffic.pcap \\\n    --router-url http://router:8080 \\\n    --verbose\n```"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/main.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_usage.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/main.py":